description: Incredibly Original 1929 Ford Model A Standard Coupe . This old car has taught me so much more than any other car I've ever owned , just learning to start the engine and the run drive gear is just fascinating to me.   I had plans for this car and was going to modify the seat so that I could drive it comfortably but have decided to leave it in its original configuration so that someone else can learn and see how it was built by Henry Ford .  It's not a high dollar car but is one that someone can drive to shows and have fun with just the way it is. This 29 was owned by the same owner until the past year and a half, I have a pile of registrations going back many years and thousands of dollars of parts that will go with the car.  It runs and drives very well, we just drive it about 20 miles in the last couple of weeks .  Please call for more info or to make an appt to see this amazing 29 Ford !  Notice it has never had the Right Rear tail light mounted , it's about as original as they come .. Clean NC Title ready to go !

description: This All Metal 1929 Ford Model A Roadster with Rumble Seat is a cool car. It has had a rebuild with some modern upgrades with that original look and running gear. The original 4 Cylinder Flathead engine has was rebuilt as was the original 3 Speed transmission. It has a modern Tilt Steering Column with a Grant GT Steering Wheel but retains the original Spark Control and has a New Alumnium Radiator to keep it running cool. Added to it was a Super Bell frontend with Rack Steering. This makes it turn easy like power steering and handle better on the road. Also added was Disc Brakes on the front to make it stop better and has a double master cylinder mounted underneath. The rear brakes are still juice brakes. Get this Roadster on the road and use the spark control to add power and it will run 70 on the Hwy good. It has a New Windshield frame and the Windshield opens out at the bottom. The headlights, taillights, brake lights and the added blinker system all works. The headlights are new. The original speedometer works as does the gas gauge and the gauge lights also work. The exterior is paint Hotrod Flat Black. The interior is nice with a Tan leather like material cover over the seat with the Rumble seat matching. It has nice black carpet on the floor. The tires are Good Year with 6:00 / 16 on front and 6:50 / 16 on rear. It has Wire Spoke wheels painted Red to give it that original look. Very fun car to drive.

description: The Ford Model A was in production from 1927 to 1931, following in the footsteps of the legendary Model T, which changed the automotive industry forever. The new and improved Model A was powered by a water-cooled 201ci (3.3L) L-Head 4-Cylinder engine mated to a 3-speed manual gearbox. It was available in over 30 different body styles but only four standard colors. This 1931 example was the final year of production and is a 2-Door Tudor Sedan, finished in Black.    The car was just tuned-up from a local classic mechanic, Verburg's Automotive of Cascade, Michigan. It starts easily, shifts smooth, and offers a unique yet simple driving experience. The car has always been stored in an indoor garage and obviously has been preserved with care over the years. Some noteworthy features include the pristine white-wall tires, the front fender-mounted spare, rear-mounted luggage rack with box, clean interior, beautiful radiator cap, and more (see photos).    This is awesome pre-war example and definitely the easiest driving car of this ear we've had the privilege to sell. The car is priced to move and will provide many future miles of enjoyment for its next owner. Call or e-mail if interested, or to make a reasonable offer. Thank you for looking.

description: GR Auto Gallery is pleased to present this 1929 rumble seat sport coupe Model A for sale.  The sport couple offers the best of both worlds, the appearance of a sporty convertible but yet it is a closed car.  The sport couple has a very distinct and classy styling.  The landau irons on the sides add a subtle but flashy look.  The rear curtain opens and folds up which allows wind to flow through the cab.  The sporty Model A wears a shiny coat of black paint with a tan pinstripe that matches the tan wire wheels.  The paint presents well.  The wire wheels are mounted to Firestone 21 inch white wall tires that really add to the look of the car.  The chrome bumpers, headlights, cluster bezel, grill shroud and grill protector all shine in the sun and present well.  The car remains in its 6 volt system.  There are aftermarket turn signals added, the “ooga” horn works as well.  The door panels and seat are covered in two tone grey material and present very well, with little to no sign of wear and tear.

The Model A has won its way into the hearts of millions of people.  This is a very clean example of the car that Henry Ford produced so many years ago.  The car has a rear mounted spare tire with a tire cover and it also has a luggage rack.  The 201 cubic inch 4 cylinder fires right up and runs as it should.  It is matted to a 3 speed manual transmission.  The car goes down the road nicely.  This clean, solid little car is ready for its next owner to run it up and down the countryside.
To see over 80 photos of this car, including under carriage please visit our website www.grautogallery.com
